==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Besayle
<hw>Be*sayle"</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>beseel</ets>, F.
<ets>bisa⟦ium⟧eul</ets>, fr. L. <ets>bis</ets> twice + LL.
<ets>avolus</ets>, dim. of L. <ets>avus</ets> grandfather.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A great-grandfather.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A kind of writ which formerly lay
where a great-grandfather died seized of lands in fee simple, and on the
day of his death a stranger abated or entered and kept the heir out.
This is now abolished.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Besaint</ent>⟦br⟧
